                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14561200" author="philipthompson" created="Wed, 27 May 2015 16:02:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve found using IntelliJ that with jdk8, at the relevant line in CFMetadata.java, that defaultValidator is an instance of CounterColumnType. With jdk7, it is an instance of o.a.c.db.marshal.BytesType.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14564779" author="carlyeks" created="Fri, 29 May 2015 13:13:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was iterating over HashMap&apos;s entries, which aren&apos;t stable between Java 7 and 8. I switched to a TreeMap instead, which will always use the first alphabetically.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14565244" author="thobbs" created="Fri, 29 May 2015 19:18:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1, committed as &lt;tt&gt;f294ee12722d074006bb3a5bc72edf2b248b1d6b&lt;/tt&gt; to 2.1 and merged up to 2.2 and trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
